WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.810 --> 00:00:06.253 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:06.253 --> 00:00:21.740 align:middle line:90%


00:00:21.740 --> 00:00:24.230 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: Dr. Jude
Currivan's life has expanded

00:00:24.230 --> 00:00:27.650 align:middle line:10%
from the UK's coal mines
to noted Oxford scholar,

00:00:27.650 --> 00:00:30.650 align:middle line:10%
with an overarching message
that links the worlds of science

00:00:30.650 --> 00:00:31.850 align:middle line:10%
and metaphysics.

00:00:31.850 --> 00:00:33.920 align:middle line:10%
She's not using science
for science's sake,

00:00:33.920 --> 00:00:36.260 align:middle line:10%
rather for bringing a
depth of knowledge that

00:00:36.260 --> 00:00:38.910 align:middle line:10%
can be applied to
transforming and healing

00:00:38.910 --> 00:00:41.120 align:middle line:10%
our planetary consciousness,
which is a very

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:43.190 align:middle line:10%
different kind of science book.

00:00:43.190 --> 00:00:45.390 align:middle line:10%
Your work is exhaustive.

00:00:45.390 --> 00:00:48.830 align:middle line:10%
You have done really
pristine research.

00:00:48.830 --> 00:00:50.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's very hard,
I would think,

00:00:50.540 --> 00:00:52.280 align:middle line:84%
for your colleagues
to argue with you,

00:00:52.280 --> 00:00:53.730 align:middle line:90%
as much as they would like to.

00:00:53.730 --> 00:00:54.530 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:00:54.530 --> 00:00:56.037 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:00:56.037 --> 00:00:58.620 align:middle line:84%
>> JUDE CURRIVAN: I think that
sums it up beautifully, Regina.

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:00.620 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now we need
to tell people the story,

00:01:00.620 --> 00:01:03.000 align:middle line:84%
so they know why
this is the case.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.490 align:middle line:10%
So first of all, as a child,
coming from an environment

00:01:07.490 --> 00:01:09.200 align:middle line:10%
where people would
go into the earth

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:11.450 align:middle line:10%
and work during the
day, what was it

00:01:11.450 --> 00:01:14.060 align:middle line:10%
that was making you kind
of shoot for the stars

00:01:14.060 --> 00:01:16.310 align:middle line:10%
in your understanding of life?

00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:19.640 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: When I was four
years old, I was in my bedroom,

00:01:19.640 --> 00:01:23.780 align:middle line:84%
and a discarnate light came into
the room and just hung there.

00:01:23.780 --> 00:01:25.650 align:middle line:90%
And I started to hear a voice.

00:01:25.650 --> 00:01:29.020 align:middle line:84%
And that voice, as it
spoke to me, fascinated me.

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And as four years old, it's
like a new toy, you know?

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:33.020 align:middle line:90%
What's going on here?

00:01:33.020 --> 00:01:35.180 align:middle line:84%
And that really began
a lifelong journey

00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:38.690 align:middle line:90%
of curiosity and discovery.

00:01:38.690 --> 00:01:40.550 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: What did
the voice say to you?

00:01:40.550 --> 00:01:43.380 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember kind of what
the feeling of the message

00:01:43.380 --> 00:01:44.180 align:middle line:90%
was at the time?

00:01:44.180 --> 00:01:46.940 align:middle line:84%
Or just that the light itself
was there speaking to you,

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:49.454 align:middle line:84%
was the inspiration,
in and of itself?

00:01:49.454 --> 00:01:51.120 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: I can't
remember the words.

00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:52.280 align:middle line:90%
It was over 60 years ago.

00:01:52.280 --> 00:01:52.410 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:53.570 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, sure.

00:01:53.570 --> 00:01:55.680 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: But it was
a very loving voice.

00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:59.030 align:middle line:10%
I just had a sense of
familiarity with it

00:01:59.030 --> 00:02:00.260 align:middle line:10%
and lovingness of it.

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:02.990 align:middle line:10%
And I know that in the
following months and years

00:02:02.990 --> 00:02:05.480 align:middle line:10%
and on, it became clearer.

00:02:05.480 --> 00:02:07.580 align:middle line:84%
But not just that
voice, but I started

00:02:07.580 --> 00:02:11.160 align:middle line:84%
to have what's called
clairaudient experiences

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:14.030 align:middle line:84%
of other beings
and intelligences.

00:02:14.030 --> 00:02:16.040 align:middle line:84%
But all sorts of
stuff was happening--

00:02:16.040 --> 00:02:19.880 align:middle line:84%
I was going out of body, I was
having precognitive dreams.

00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:22.460 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I was really
walking between worlds.

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:23.690 align:middle line:10%
And for me, it was natural.

00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:25.976 align:middle line:10%
It wasn't something strange.

00:02:25.976 --> 00:02:27.350 align:middle line:84%
It was almost like
opening a door

00:02:27.350 --> 00:02:29.690 align:middle line:84%
and just walking into
somewhere different.

00:02:29.690 --> 00:02:32.420 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
I was fascinated.

00:02:32.420 --> 00:02:35.750 align:middle line:84%
I became fascinated
by the stars.

00:02:35.750 --> 00:02:39.200 align:middle line:84%
We lived in a
council house, which

00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:41.680 align:middle line:84%
is where the local council
subsidizes housing.

00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:42.990 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, very modest.

00:02:42.990 --> 00:02:44.630 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Very modest.

00:02:44.630 --> 00:02:47.090 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, we had street
lights, but still,

00:02:47.090 --> 00:02:49.606 align:middle line:84%
not enough to stop me from
being able to see the stars.

00:02:49.606 --> 00:02:50.480 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Lucky you.

00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:51.552 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Lucky me.

00:02:51.552 --> 00:02:53.510 align:middle line:84%
And where I live now, we
have no street lights,

00:02:53.510 --> 00:02:55.430 align:middle line:90%
so we have a very clear sky.

00:02:55.430 --> 00:02:57.260 align:middle line:84%
But I was just
fascinated by the stars.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:00.140 align:middle line:84%
I always had a sense
of, again, familiarity.

00:03:00.140 --> 00:03:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And somehow we
were all connected.

00:03:03.440 --> 00:03:07.700 align:middle line:84%
And that took me down a
journey of exploration,

00:03:07.700 --> 00:03:09.710 align:middle line:90%
of scientific discovery.

00:03:09.710 --> 00:03:13.070 align:middle line:84%
Because I wanted to
understand the why of what

00:03:13.070 --> 00:03:15.260 align:middle line:84%
was all of this,
but also the how.

00:03:15.260 --> 00:03:19.640 align:middle line:84%
How did these experiences
that seem to be unusual--

00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:22.190 align:middle line:84%
and I shared very little
with anybody at the time.

00:03:22.190 --> 00:03:23.774 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't that
I was scared to.

00:03:23.774 --> 00:03:25.440 align:middle line:84%
I was just having too
much fun, I think.

00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:26.312 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right?

00:03:26.312 --> 00:03:28.020 align:middle line:84%
You didn't want anyone
to ruin your fun--

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:28.250 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: No.

00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:29.350 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want anybody
to ruin my fun--

00:03:29.350 --> 00:03:29.720 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --by questioning it.

00:03:29.720 --> 00:03:30.910 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: --by
questioning it.

00:03:30.910 --> 00:03:32.284 align:middle line:84%
And I suppose
there was something

00:03:32.284 --> 00:03:35.210 align:middle line:84%
in me that perhaps
subconsciously I

00:03:35.210 --> 00:03:37.280 align:middle line:90%
had that fear that they might.

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:39.470 align:middle line:84%
I know my mom wouldn't
have had that problem,

00:03:39.470 --> 00:03:40.980 align:middle line:90%
but perhaps others might.

00:03:40.980 --> 00:03:44.190 align:middle line:84%
So on that subconscious
level, I never shared widely.

00:03:44.190 --> 00:03:47.510 align:middle line:84%
But I just wanted
to understand how

00:03:47.510 --> 00:03:50.720 align:middle line:84%
what we call physical
reality somehow

00:03:50.720 --> 00:03:55.820 align:middle line:84%
emerged from this bigger,
deeper, wider reality

00:03:55.820 --> 00:03:57.800 align:middle line:84%
that I was directly
experiencing.

00:03:57.800 --> 00:04:01.310 align:middle line:84%
So I started to study
science as a language,

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:03.650 align:middle line:84%
as a language to try
and help me understand

00:04:03.650 --> 00:04:10.950 align:middle line:84%
how the physical world somehow
emerged from this bigger world.

00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:14.140 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And did you find
your answers while studying

00:04:14.140 --> 00:04:14.980 align:middle line:90%
at university?

00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:15.780 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: No.

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:18.430 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] Almost the opposite.

00:04:18.430 --> 00:04:21.709 align:middle line:84%
I was at Oxford in the
'70s, the early '70s.

00:04:21.709 --> 00:04:27.070 align:middle line:84%
And I was almost shocked to
see that the physical realm was

00:04:27.070 --> 00:04:29.760 align:middle line:84%
the only realm that
was being considered

00:04:29.760 --> 00:04:33.140 align:middle line:84%
and that you weren't
to stray beyond that.

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:37.870 align:middle line:84%
Even though, specializing in
quantum physics, of course,

00:04:37.870 --> 00:04:40.840 align:middle line:84%
I realized that quantum physics
doesn't work unless there's

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:42.700 align:middle line:90%
a deeper level of reality.

00:04:42.700 --> 00:04:46.630 align:middle line:84%
Quantum physics doesn't work
unless our entire universe

00:04:46.630 --> 00:04:49.660 align:middle line:84%
is interconnected at
a very profound level.

00:04:49.660 --> 00:04:52.060 align:middle line:84%
But those aspects of it
were so peripheralized.

00:04:52.060 --> 00:04:58.000 align:middle line:84%
And so it was taught in a
very physicalized perspective.

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:00.359 align:middle line:84%
I also specialized
in relativity,

00:05:00.359 --> 00:05:01.900 align:middle line:84%
because I was looking
at the biggest.

00:05:01.900 --> 00:05:03.890 align:middle line:90%
Again, the same things.

00:05:03.890 --> 00:05:07.810 align:middle line:84%
Relativity is showing
that, of course,

00:05:07.810 --> 00:05:10.390 align:middle line:84%
time is relative to
an observer, space

00:05:10.390 --> 00:05:15.040 align:middle line:84%
is relative to an observer, but
together they are invariant.

00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:18.382 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, our universe couldn't
exist and evolve together--

00:05:18.382 --> 00:05:19.590 align:middle line:90%
the laws of physics couldn't.

00:05:19.590 --> 00:05:21.442 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And that's
difficult for science.

00:05:21.442 --> 00:05:23.150 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: It is
difficult for science,

00:05:23.150 --> 00:05:28.440 align:middle line:84%
because the methodology of
science for 300 years has said,

00:05:28.440 --> 00:05:32.330 align:middle line:84%
look, I'm a scientist, I'm
going to experiment on this.

00:05:32.330 --> 00:05:34.010 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to look at this.

00:05:34.010 --> 00:05:35.850 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to try
and understand it.

00:05:35.850 --> 00:05:38.090 align:middle line:90%
And science is very good--

00:05:38.090 --> 00:05:39.980 align:middle line:90%
that methodology is great--

00:05:39.980 --> 00:05:45.090 align:middle line:84%
at taking stuff apart and
trying to find what makes it up,

00:05:45.090 --> 00:05:46.750 align:middle line:90%
what its constituents are--

00:05:46.750 --> 00:05:49.010 align:middle line:90%
smaller and smaller and smaller.

00:05:49.010 --> 00:05:52.220 align:middle line:84%
But rather like-- and he'll
hate me for saying this.

00:05:52.220 --> 00:05:54.890 align:middle line:84%
My brother used to be
really good at taking things

00:05:54.890 --> 00:05:56.992 align:middle line:84%
like watches and clocks
apart, but he could never

00:05:56.992 --> 00:05:58.200 align:middle line:90%
put them back together again.

00:05:58.200 --> 00:05:59.392 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:05:59.392 --> 00:06:02.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
scientific methodology's

00:06:02.160 --> 00:06:05.510 align:middle line:90%
great at taking the bits apart.

00:06:05.510 --> 00:06:07.460 align:middle line:84%
But as Deepak Chopra
once said, it's

00:06:07.460 --> 00:06:09.770 align:middle line:84%
like taking a radio
apart, and then wondering

00:06:09.770 --> 00:06:11.870 align:middle line:90%
where the music's gone to.

00:06:11.870 --> 00:06:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's now changing,
but it's quite a leap.

00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:18.800 align:middle line:84%
And also it requires
modifications

00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:21.790 align:middle line:84%
to the scientific
methodologies that are still

00:06:21.790 --> 00:06:23.434 align:middle line:90%
at their very early stages.

00:06:23.434 --> 00:06:24.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:26.210 align:middle line:84%
And quantum
physicists are really

00:06:26.210 --> 00:06:28.130 align:middle line:84%
considered kind of the
outcasts and renegades

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:30.719 align:middle line:84%
of the world of science for
the most part anyway, right?

00:06:30.719 --> 00:06:31.760 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: To a degree.

00:06:31.760 --> 00:06:33.440 align:middle line:84%
But the other part
of that, they're

00:06:33.440 --> 00:06:35.780 align:middle line:90%
like sort of honored geeks.

00:06:35.780 --> 00:06:39.550 align:middle line:84%
Because everybody knows that
at the most fundamental level,

00:06:39.550 --> 00:06:42.530 align:middle line:84%
the quantum understanding is
crucial to our understanding

00:06:42.530 --> 00:06:43.680 align:middle line:90%
of physical reality.

00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:45.740 align:middle line:84%
The problem with the
quantum physicists

00:06:45.740 --> 00:06:48.680 align:middle line:84%
are that quantum
physics describes

00:06:48.680 --> 00:06:50.870 align:middle line:84%
the behavior of
energy and matter,

00:06:50.870 --> 00:06:53.820 align:middle line:84%
and now we know
they're equivalent.

00:06:53.820 --> 00:06:56.480 align:middle line:84%
But the problem with
that is energy and matter

00:06:56.480 --> 00:06:58.105 align:middle line:90%
have no sense of time.

00:06:58.105 --> 00:06:59.480 align:middle line:84%
They don't care
whether something

00:06:59.480 --> 00:07:01.260 align:middle line:90%
runs that way or that way.

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:04.370 align:middle line:84%
So the quantum physicists
don't really, in the main,

00:07:04.370 --> 00:07:06.800 align:middle line:90%
understand the nature of time.

00:07:06.800 --> 00:07:11.420 align:middle line:84%
What investigates time
is relativity theory.

00:07:11.420 --> 00:07:13.910 align:middle line:84%
And you need to actually,
in my perspective--

00:07:13.910 --> 00:07:15.830 align:middle line:84%
and this is what I've
done in the book--

00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:21.080 align:middle line:84%
if you restate the laws of
physics as laws of information,

00:07:21.080 --> 00:07:23.570 align:middle line:84%
and if you start
even further back,

00:07:23.570 --> 00:07:25.970 align:middle line:84%
back into the mid-19th
century with something called

00:07:25.970 --> 00:07:29.230 align:middle line:84%
thermodynamics, which is
the behavior of gases,

00:07:29.230 --> 00:07:32.780 align:middle line:84%
you can bring all of the
discoveries since then--

00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:37.010 align:middle line:84%
quantum and relativity--
and actually understand

00:07:37.010 --> 00:07:40.100 align:middle line:84%
that when you restate those
two laws of thermodynamics

00:07:40.100 --> 00:07:43.310 align:middle line:84%
to two laws of
information, you get

00:07:43.310 --> 00:07:45.620 align:middle line:84%
quantum mechanics
and relativity theory

00:07:45.620 --> 00:07:48.600 align:middle line:84%
as free- you get them for free--
and you can reconcile them.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:49.400 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:07:49.400 --> 00:07:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And reconciliation has been
really your dharma of sorts.

00:07:54.410 --> 00:07:57.350 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you've been trying
to reconcile philosophy,

00:07:57.350 --> 00:08:01.250 align:middle line:90%
physics, science, spirituality.

00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:03.500 align:middle line:84%
That's a tall task,
but you really

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:05.330 align:middle line:90%
have been successful in this.

00:08:05.330 --> 00:08:08.540 align:middle line:90%


00:08:08.540 --> 00:08:11.450 align:middle line:84%
What was it
personally in you that

00:08:11.450 --> 00:08:15.270 align:middle line:84%
needed this deep reconciliation
yourself to create--

00:08:15.270 --> 00:08:17.240 align:middle line:84%
because there is a type
of cognitive dissonance

00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:18.406 align:middle line:90%
when you have an experience.

00:08:18.406 --> 00:08:20.210 align:middle line:84%
And you say, I
know this is real,

00:08:20.210 --> 00:08:22.822 align:middle line:84%
but then your background
says, no, this is not real.

00:08:22.822 --> 00:08:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And it can create a
cognitive dissonance.

00:08:24.530 --> 00:08:26.960 align:middle line:84%
And I know a lot of
scientists suffer from this,

00:08:26.960 --> 00:08:29.690 align:middle line:84%
because others have
too had experiences.

00:08:29.690 --> 00:08:31.090 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Exactly right.

00:08:31.090 --> 00:08:33.200 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
very important.

00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:35.299 align:middle line:84%
For me, I never had the
cognitive dissonance,

00:08:35.299 --> 00:08:37.700 align:middle line:90%
because I started so young.

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:40.070 align:middle line:84%
It was like a dance
of exploration.

00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:43.900 align:middle line:84%
And realizing that to
dance, I needed both legs.

00:08:43.900 --> 00:08:46.390 align:middle line:84%
I needed both left hemisphere
and right hemisphere.

00:08:46.390 --> 00:08:49.100 align:middle line:84%
But also, I never
felt-- and, of course,

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:52.580 align:middle line:84%
when you go back to ancient
times and the sacred science

00:08:52.580 --> 00:08:55.940 align:middle line:84%
of the Egyptians and the sacred
science of the Vedic sages

00:08:55.940 --> 00:09:01.580 align:middle line:84%
of India, we're now describing--
and in "The Cosmic Hologram"

00:09:01.580 --> 00:09:05.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm describing-- something that
the ancient Vedic sages would

00:09:05.760 --> 00:09:06.560 align:middle line:90%
have recognized.

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:09.210 align:middle line:10%
Because they refer
to it as Indra's Net.

00:09:09.210 --> 00:09:11.660 align:middle line:10%
So now we're almost
looping back,

00:09:11.660 --> 00:09:14.660 align:middle line:10%
but we're going
forward to realize

00:09:14.660 --> 00:09:19.310 align:middle line:10%
that those ancients had
immense intuitive experiential

00:09:19.310 --> 00:09:20.570 align:middle line:10%
insights.

00:09:20.570 --> 00:09:22.070 align:middle line:90%
We've moved forward.

00:09:22.070 --> 00:09:25.640 align:middle line:84%
We've also taken a
bit of a side route--

00:09:25.640 --> 00:09:28.190 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Into a world
of extreme materialism.

00:09:28.190 --> 00:09:30.380 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN:
Extreme materialism.

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:32.750 align:middle line:84%
And it's because our
beliefs drive our behaviors

00:09:32.750 --> 00:09:36.530 align:middle line:84%
that extreme materialism
and that myth of separation

00:09:36.530 --> 00:09:38.570 align:middle line:84%
has driven our
dysfunctional behavior.

00:09:38.570 --> 00:09:41.450 align:middle line:84%
