You've done it.

00:10:57.440 --> 00:10:57.730 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Thank you.

00:10:57.730 --> 00:10:58.938 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Let's get into it.

00:10:58.938 --> 00:11:02.085 align:middle line:84%
You use the word information
hyphenated-- in-formation.

00:11:02.085 --> 00:11:03.560 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: That's right.

00:11:03.560 --> 00:11:05.584 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Just start
from there-- why?

00:11:05.584 --> 00:11:08.000 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: Because we think
we know what information is,

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:11.960 align:middle line:84%
because information is the
basis of all our technologies.

00:11:11.960 --> 00:11:15.290 align:middle line:84%
And what we do is
with information, we--

00:11:15.290 --> 00:11:17.960 align:middle line:84%
for example, now
in our interview,

00:11:17.960 --> 00:11:21.250 align:middle line:84%
the camera is taking
photographs of us

00:11:21.250 --> 00:11:22.730 align:middle line:90%
from the light reflected on it.

00:11:22.730 --> 00:11:24.710 align:middle line:84%
It's transferring
all that information

00:11:24.710 --> 00:11:25.940 align:middle line:90%
into digitized bits--

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:27.740 align:middle line:90%
ones and zeros.

00:11:27.740 --> 00:11:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Anything in reality
can be described

00:11:31.970 --> 00:11:35.300 align:middle line:84%
in strings of ones and zeros,
but those ones and zeros

00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:37.940 align:middle line:90%
of themselves are data.

00:11:37.940 --> 00:11:41.220 align:middle line:84%
It's not really meaningful,
unless we put it together.

00:11:41.220 --> 00:11:43.790 align:middle line:84%
So instead of just
saying information,

00:11:43.790 --> 00:11:45.590 align:middle line:84%
which you could think
of as just being

00:11:45.590 --> 00:11:51.170 align:middle line:84%
random data, by hyphenating
in-formation, what I'm saying

00:11:51.170 --> 00:11:54.890 align:middle line:84%
is our universe and everything
in it is not random.

00:11:54.890 --> 00:11:56.380 align:middle line:90%
It is interrelation.

00:11:56.380 --> 00:11:57.630 align:middle line:90%
It is dynamic.

00:11:57.630 --> 00:11:59.160 align:middle line:90%
It is meaningful.

00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:01.490 align:middle line:84%
It is essentially
alive, way beyond

00:12:01.490 --> 00:12:04.270 align:middle line:90%
the biological term of that.

00:12:04.270 --> 00:12:06.020 align:middle line:90%
And so it's patterned.

00:12:06.020 --> 00:12:08.930 align:middle line:84%
It's intentionally patterned
and meaningful and purposeful.

00:12:08.930 --> 00:12:11.765 align:middle line:84%
So it's like, if we
have an alphabet--

00:12:11.765 --> 00:12:15.740 align:middle line:84%
A and B and C-- they have
no meaning of themselves.

00:12:15.740 --> 00:12:18.530 align:middle line:84%
But if we start to put
them together in words,

00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:21.380 align:middle line:84%
and then we start to put those
words in terms of sentences,

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:26.730 align:middle line:84%
and those sentences in terms
of poems and plays and songs,

00:12:26.730 --> 00:12:28.170 align:middle line:90%
then that's meaningful.

00:12:28.170 --> 00:12:31.702 align:middle line:84%
So our universe,
essentially, is a song.

00:12:31.702 --> 00:12:34.830 align:middle line:84%
It is a meaningful song
that exists and evolves--

00:12:34.830 --> 00:12:36.160 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It has harmonics.

00:12:36.160 --> 00:12:37.640 align:middle line:90%
It has a melody.

00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:38.440 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Yes.

00:12:38.440 --> 00:12:39.820 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:41.580 align:middle line:84%
I just love the way
your mind works.

00:12:41.580 --> 00:12:45.160 align:middle line:84%
So you're saying that
universal physicality

00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:48.430 align:middle line:84%
is a matter of the flows
of this information

00:12:48.430 --> 00:12:51.900 align:middle line:84%
in various processes
of creation.

00:12:51.900 --> 00:12:56.860 align:middle line:84%
So for people who are
visual, paint a picture--

00:12:56.860 --> 00:12:58.030 align:middle line:90%
or make a song, either one--

00:12:58.030 --> 00:12:58.870 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:12:58.870 --> 00:13:00.369 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: You
don't hear me sing.

00:13:00.369 --> 00:13:01.625 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:13:01.625 --> 00:13:05.255 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --of how this
flows, what this looks like.

00:13:05.255 --> 00:13:07.630 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: Well, perhaps we
can go back to have a sense

00:13:07.630 --> 00:13:10.690 align:middle line:84%
of its beginning, 13.8
billion years ago.

00:13:10.690 --> 00:13:14.530 align:middle line:10%
Because we know that
our universe began as--

00:13:14.530 --> 00:13:17.860 align:middle line:10%
and now, and what I'm saying
in "The Cosmic Hologram,"

00:13:17.860 --> 00:13:23.082 align:middle line:10%
is that our universe, and other
universes perhaps, are finite.

00:13:23.082 --> 00:13:25.570 align:middle line:84%
They're finite entities
in an infinity,

00:13:25.570 --> 00:13:27.790 align:middle line:90%
an eternity of cosmic mind.

00:13:27.790 --> 00:13:30.730 align:middle line:84%
And actually, Stephen
Hawking posthumously

00:13:30.730 --> 00:13:34.750 align:middle line:84%
