physical solidity is incredibly

00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:45.160 align:middle line:90%
ephemeral.

00:15:45.160 --> 00:15:47.940 align:middle line:84%
And then when physicists
have drilled down

00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:51.790 align:middle line:84%
to tinier and tinier scales,
to atomic scales and smaller,

00:15:51.790 --> 00:15:55.930 align:middle line:84%
we realize that everything
we call solid materiality

00:15:55.930 --> 00:15:57.810 align:middle line:90%
is 99.999999.

00:15:57.810 --> 00:15:59.262 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly, 9999.

00:15:59.262 --> 00:16:00.470 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: "No-thing-ness."

00:16:00.470 --> 00:16:01.761 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Nothing, yes, space.

00:16:01.761 --> 00:16:05.070 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: And what remains
is actually relational

00:16:05.070 --> 00:16:06.640 align:middle line:90%
excitations.

00:16:06.640 --> 00:16:08.820 align:middle line:90%
But the key to this--

00:16:08.820 --> 00:16:11.370 align:middle line:84%
and I'm taking it over
the bridge as it were--

00:16:11.370 --> 00:16:13.980 align:middle line:84%
is that we also
realize information

00:16:13.980 --> 00:16:16.290 align:middle line:84%
is as physically
real as anything

00:16:16.290 --> 00:16:18.090 align:middle line:90%
we call energy and matter.

00:16:18.090 --> 00:16:20.340 align:middle line:84%
And there have been experiments
to show this recently.

00:16:20.340 --> 00:16:22.830 align:middle line:84%
Some years ago,
theorists were already

00:16:22.830 --> 00:16:27.420 align:middle line:84%
showing or really
hypothesizing that when

00:16:27.420 --> 00:16:31.680 align:middle line:84%
we stored or deleted
one bit of information

00:16:31.680 --> 00:16:35.400 align:middle line:84%
that it involved physical
parameters, such as work

00:16:35.400 --> 00:16:36.420 align:middle line:90%
and heat.

00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:40.120 align:middle line:84%
And more recently, we've been
able to experimentally show

00:16:40.120 --> 00:16:40.920 align:middle line:90%
that.

00:16:40.920 --> 00:16:43.170 align:middle line:84%
So we know that it's
not just the way

00:16:43.170 --> 00:16:46.490 align:middle line:84%
that digitized
information is held

00:16:46.490 --> 00:16:49.110 align:middle line:84%
and comes into friction with
cables or anything else.

00:16:49.110 --> 00:16:49.980 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:16:49.980 --> 00:16:55.260 align:middle line:84%
It's the information itself is
as physically real as anything

00:16:55.260 --> 00:16:57.630 align:middle line:90%
we call energy and matter.

00:16:57.630 --> 00:17:01.660 align:middle line:84%
So information is more
fundamental than energy matter.

00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:04.230 align:middle line:84%
It's more fundamental
than spacetime.

00:17:04.230 --> 00:17:07.260 align:middle line:84%
It's expressed in
complementary ways as both,

00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:12.210 align:middle line:84%
but it shows how that deeper,
fundamental consciousness,

00:17:12.210 --> 00:17:16.690 align:middle line:84%
intelligence of the cosmos,
can give rise to a thought

00:17:16.690 --> 00:17:18.340 align:middle line:90%
form that is our universe.

00:17:18.340 --> 00:17:19.140 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:19.140 --> 00:17:23.130 align:middle line:84%
So if we're looking at it
through a material lens

00:17:23.130 --> 00:17:27.540 align:middle line:84%
