it shines a light on an object,

00:21:19.850 --> 00:21:20.650 align:middle line:90%
any object.

00:21:20.650 --> 00:21:21.730 align:middle line:90%
It could be this cup of tea.

00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:22.530 align:middle line:90%
It could be you.

00:21:22.530 --> 00:21:23.870 align:middle line:90%
It could be anything.

00:21:23.870 --> 00:21:28.150 align:middle line:10%
It captures the information
from that 3D object,

00:21:28.150 --> 00:21:31.800 align:middle line:10%
and it projects it on a
two-dimensional film or screen.

00:21:31.800 --> 00:21:35.020 align:middle line:10%
So all the data's captured,
but that 3D object is now

00:21:35.020 --> 00:21:37.270 align:middle line:10%
captured on a 2D screen.

00:21:37.270 --> 00:21:41.020 align:middle line:84%
Then, when a light is shone
through that 2D screen,

00:21:41.020 --> 00:21:45.370 align:middle line:84%
the 3D hologram of the
object is projected.

00:21:45.370 --> 00:21:47.350 align:middle line:84%
And we're now coming
to a point where

00:21:47.350 --> 00:21:49.130 align:middle line:84%
we can have
immersive holography,

00:21:49.130 --> 00:21:51.430 align:middle line:84%
and people can move
around holograms,

00:21:51.430 --> 00:21:54.980 align:middle line:84%
and with ultrasonics, can
actually touch holograms.

00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:59.290 align:middle line:84%
So we're getting more and
more familiar with reality, 3D

00:21:59.290 --> 00:22:02.770 align:middle line:90%
reality, through 2D holograms--

00:22:02.770 --> 00:22:04.130 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Being projected.

00:22:04.130 --> 00:22:08.320 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: --recreated
