under its own weight.

00:22:18.170 --> 00:22:21.100 align:middle line:84%
And it needed to be a massive
star under its own weight.

00:22:21.100 --> 00:22:23.890 align:middle line:84%
The force of gravity
was so strong

00:22:23.890 --> 00:22:28.050 align:middle line:84%
that it continued to fall
in on itself beyond a point,

00:22:28.050 --> 00:22:31.460 align:middle line:84%
called the event horizon,
where even light could escape--

00:22:31.460 --> 00:22:33.240 align:middle line:90%
hence, black hole.

00:22:33.240 --> 00:22:35.960 align:middle line:84%
But the question then was, what
happened to all the information

00:22:35.960 --> 00:22:37.390 align:middle line:90%
in the star?

00:22:37.390 --> 00:22:40.760 align:middle line:84%
And what it was realized, is
that instead of being lost,

00:22:40.760 --> 00:22:45.196 align:middle line:84%
