00:38:39.890 --> 00:38:40.690 align:middle line:90%
experiences--

00:38:40.690 --> 00:38:42.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, I've
been in his workshops.

00:38:42.180 --> 00:38:43.020 align:middle line:90%
It's really fun.

00:38:43.020 --> 00:38:43.535 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: It's great.

00:38:43.535 --> 00:38:45.450 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It's really
interesting to see how

00:38:45.450 --> 00:38:47.021 align:middle line:84%
functional his
theories actually are.

00:38:47.021 --> 00:38:48.020 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Absolutely.

00:38:48.020 --> 00:38:51.510 align:middle line:84%
And he's just given me a lovely
endorsement for the book,

00:38:51.510 --> 00:38:53.580 align:middle line:84%
because he knows
that what this is

00:38:53.580 --> 00:38:57.480 align:middle line:84%
is the emergent bigger picture
framework that absolutely

00:38:57.480 --> 00:39:00.870 align:middle line:84%
validates what he's been
finding, and many, many others.

00:39:00.870 --> 00:39:04.480 align:middle line:84%
So the future is
becoming crystallized

00:39:04.480 --> 00:39:06.850 align:middle line:84%
as it comes to the
present moment.

00:39:06.850 --> 00:39:10.080 align:middle line:84%
But that potentizing,
that potentiality,

00:39:10.080 --> 00:39:14.610 align:middle line:84%
those new attractors of
greater coherence of emergence

00:39:14.610 --> 00:39:17.740 align:middle line:84%
are potentizing, and
not in the physical,

00:39:17.740 --> 00:39:21.720 align:middle line:84%
but in this more
foundational realm

00:39:21.720 --> 00:39:26.000 align:middle line:84%
of possibility and experience
and evolutionary impulse.

00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:29.960 align:middle line:84%
So as they crystallize,
they come to us

00:39:29.960 --> 00:39:35.220 align:middle line:84%
so that that template is there
just before we essentially

00:39:35.220 --> 00:39:36.520 align:middle line:90%
step into it.

00:39:36.520 --> 00:39:37.320 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:39:37.320 --> 00:39:42.182 align:middle line:84%
And that would be, so to
speak, a co-creative reality.

00:39:42.182 --> 00:39:43.140 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Very much.

00:39:43.140 --> 00:39:45.098 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But is there
something that precedes

00:39:45.098 --> 00:39:46.710 align:middle line:90%
the co-creative reality?

00:39:46.710 --> 00:39:50.400 align:middle line:84%
Is there a great mind
within-- or many great minds

00:39:50.400 --> 00:39:54.840 align:middle line:84%
within the cosmos that have the
potential of visioning thought

00:39:54.840 --> 00:39:59.040 align:middle line:84%
at a certain level
that's perhaps

00:39:59.040 --> 00:40:01.680 align:middle line:84%
beyond our comprehension, a
certain level of creativity?

00:40:01.680 --> 00:40:03.270 align:middle line:84%
Just as our level
of creativity would

00:40:03.270 --> 00:40:06.360 align:middle line:90%
be probably foreign to an ant.

00:40:06.360 --> 00:40:09.690 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: Yes, I mean,
Einstein talked about cosmic

00:40:09.690 --> 00:40:10.860 align:middle line:90%
mind.

00:40:10.860 --> 00:40:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's very much
my perspective--

00:40:12.720 --> 00:40:14.520 align:middle line:84%
that everything
we call reality--

00:40:14.520 --> 00:40:17.510 align:middle line:84%
and many realities we
have no comprehension of--

00:40:17.510 --> 00:40:22.800 align:middle line:84%
but the source of all
being is an infinite

00:40:22.800 --> 00:40:27.760 align:middle line:84%
and eternal cosmic mind and that
universes are finite thought

00:40:27.760 --> 00:40:28.560 align:middle line:90%
forms.

00:40:28.560 --> 00:40:29.640 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes, exactly.

00:40:29.640 --> 00:40:33.360 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: --in that
infinite eternal mind.

00:40:33.360 --> 00:40:38.370 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But that word gets
basically translated into many

00:40:38.370 --> 00:40:41.130 align:middle line:84%
other words, and that's where
science becomes frightened.

00:40:41.130 --> 00:40:42.360 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Yes.

00:40:42.360 --> 00:40:45.660 align:middle line:84%
And my sense is that
science has an opportunity

00:40:45.660 --> 00:40:47.160 align:middle line:84%
to be really part
of the solution.

00:40:47.160 --> 00:40:51.360 align:middle line:84%
Because, for me, this is
so exciting and has so many

00:40:51.360 --> 00:40:53.880 align:middle line:84%
opportunities for
science to grow up--

00:40:53.880 --> 00:40:56.250 align:middle line:84%
as well as us growing
up, collectively--

00:40:56.250 --> 00:40:59.640 align:middle line:84%
I feel science itself and its
methodologies can grow up.

00:40:59.640 --> 00:41:01.500 align:middle line:90%
And there is a way forward.

00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:03.660 align:middle line:10%
Another friend of mine,
Professor Max Velmans,

00:41:03.660 --> 00:41:06.140 align:middle line:10%
wrote a book called
"Understanding Consciousness."

00:41:06.140 --> 00:41:07.590 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote in
that how we could

00:41:07.590 --> 00:41:09.870 align:middle line:84%
expand the scientific
methodology

00:41:09.870 --> 00:41:13.230 align:middle line:84%
to be both the first person
and the third person.

00:41:13.230 --> 00:41:14.880 align:middle line:10%
Because the problem
is that science

00:41:14.880 --> 00:41:17.430 align:middle line:10%
has just tried to see
everything from a third person

00:41:17.430 --> 00:41:18.870 align:middle line:10%
perspective.

00:41:18.870 --> 00:41:21.960 align:middle line:84%
But we now realize, as
everything is interconnected

00:41:21.960 --> 00:41:24.700 align:middle line:84%
and reality is
essentially unified,

00:41:24.700 --> 00:41:26.850 align:middle line:84%
that we have to
actually bring together

00:41:26.850 --> 00:41:31.984 align:middle line:84%
that first person perspective of
reality with that third person.

00:41:31.984 --> 00:41:33.900 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, you and
I could change places.

00:41:33.900 --> 00:41:38.100 align:middle line:84%
If I was a scientist trying to
understand what was going on

00:41:38.100 --> 00:41:42.360 align:middle line:84%
within you or how
you see the world,

00:41:42.360 --> 00:41:44.490 align:middle line:84%
you would have your
first person perspective,

00:41:44.490 --> 00:41:47.550 align:middle line:84%
I would have the third
person, looking at you

00:41:47.550 --> 00:41:51.020 align:middle line:84%
and measuring you and whatever
I would or hearing your story.

00:41:51.020 --> 00:41:52.470 align:middle line:90%
But we could swap places--

00:41:52.470 --> 00:41:56.130 align:middle line:84%
you could put the white coat on
and I could sit in your jeans.

00:41:56.130 --> 00:41:58.930 align:middle line:84%
And you could be the scientist
saying, oh, I can measure this.

00:41:58.930 --> 00:42:00.265 align:middle line:90%
I can see this.

00:42:00.265 --> 00:42:02.600 align:middle line:10%
Now, Jude, what are
you experiencing?

00:42:02.600 --> 00:42:04.070 align:middle line:90%
We need to bring them together.

00:42:04.070 --> 00:42:06.590 align:middle line:84%
And there's a scientific
way of doing that, but it's

00:42:06.590 --> 00:42:08.760 align:middle line:84%
a science that recognizes
that consciousness

00:42:08.760 --> 00:42:10.520 align:middle line:84%
isn't what we have, it's what
we in the hard world are.

00:42:10.520 --> 00:42:11.360 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Are.

00:42:11.360 --> 00:42:16.100 align:middle line:84%
And this has been perturbing
to a lot of scientists,

00:42:16.100 --> 00:42:17.420 align:middle line:90%
because it's a missing element.

00:42:17.420 --> 00:42:20.720 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness is the
answer to the solution

00:42:20.720 --> 00:42:22.880 align:middle line:84%
they're looking for, but
they will not go there.

00:42:22.880 --> 00:42:25.100 align:middle line:84%
And it almost seems
as though as long

00:42:25.100 --> 00:42:29.514 align:middle line:84%
as we remain within a
materialistic reference--

00:42:29.514 --> 00:42:30.430 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: We can't.

00:42:30.430 --> 00:42:33.470 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --that you can have
somehow control and mastery

00:42:33.470 --> 00:42:36.530 align:middle line:90%
over the material world.

00:42:36.530 --> 00:42:38.000 align:middle line:84%
And if you look
to something that

00:42:38.000 --> 00:42:41.480 align:middle line:84%
is far greater in its
thought form capabilities,

00:42:41.480 --> 00:42:44.870 align:middle line:84%
you would be reduced
to something less than

00:42:44.870 --> 00:42:47.540 align:middle line:84%
rather than understanding
you're a co-creative part

00:42:47.540 --> 00:42:50.750 align:middle line:84%
of that very thing, and you
can even be more than anything

00:42:50.750 --> 00:42:53.510 align:middle line:84%
the material world
ever had to offer you

00:42:53.510 --> 00:42:55.635 align:middle line:84%
in your systems of
control as a scientist.

00:42:55.635 --> 00:42:56.510 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Exactly.

00:42:56.510 --> 00:42:59.615 align:middle line:84%
And not just as a scientist, but
as a person, as a human being.

00:42:59.615 --> 00:42:59.900 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And as a person.

00:42:59.900 --> 00:43:00.620 align:middle line:90%
Right, of course.

00:43:00.620 --> 00:43:02.780 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: Because I
think this is exactly that.

00:43:02.780 --> 00:43:05.560 align:middle line:90%
This is so empowering.

00:43:05.560 --> 00:43:08.094 align:middle line:84%
Materialistic reductionism
and this myth of separation--

00:43:08.094 --> 00:43:09.260 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It's so limiting.

00:43:09.260 --> 00:43:10.910 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: --it's so limiting.

00:43:10.910 --> 00:43:14.765 align:middle line:84%
And when we are able to
understand this and experience

00:43:14.765 --> 00:43:16.240 align:middle line:90%
it and embody it--

00:43:16.240 --> 00:43:17.360 align:middle line:90%
my goodness.

00:43:17.360 --> 00:43:20.660 align:middle line:84%
I just feel as a
species, we're like when

00:43:20.660 --> 00:43:23.630 align:middle line:84%
you and I were three years old,
and it was first day of school.

00:43:23.630 --> 00:43:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And we hadn't even
learned about writing,

00:43:27.260 --> 00:43:29.060 align:middle line:90%
let alone joined up writing.

00:43:29.060 --> 00:43:33.830 align:middle line:84%
So as a species, we have
gone through these spirals

00:43:33.830 --> 00:43:36.590 align:middle line:90%
of remembering, dismembering.

00:43:36.590 --> 00:43:40.040 align:middle line:84%
And I hope and trust that we're
on this verge of remembering.

00:43:40.040 --> 00:43:44.870 align:middle line:84%
But this remembering, I feel,
is a leap of conscious evolution

00:43:44.870 --> 00:43:47.360 align:middle line:90%
that is--

00:43:47.360 --> 00:43:50.420 align:middle line:84%
I can't even really
imagine what it could be.

00:43:50.420 --> 00:43:52.850 align:middle line:84%
But even to really
become galactic humans,

00:43:52.850 --> 00:43:56.480 align:middle line:84%
universal humans,
actual, conscious,

00:43:56.480 --> 00:44:00.290 align:middle line:84%
microcosmic creators
with our universe's

00:44:00.290 --> 00:44:01.610 align:middle line:90%
evolutionary impulse.

00:44:01.610 --> 00:44:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:44:02.720 --> 00:44:06.530 align:middle line:84%
And looking at these waves
of consciousness-- expansion,

00:44:06.530 --> 00:44:09.440 align:middle line:84%
contraction, remembering,
dismembering--

00:44:09.440 --> 00:44:13.239 align:middle line:84%
hundreds of years ago, the
scientists were philosophers--

00:44:13.239 --> 00:44:14.530 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Indeed, they were.

00:44:14.530 --> 00:44:14.990 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --by nature.

00:44:14.990 --> 00:44:16.370 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: They were called
natural philosophers before

00:44:16.370 --> 00:44:17.720 align:middle line:90%
they were called scientists.

00:44:17.720 --> 00:44:21.740 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And so what
that did is it gave context

00:44:21.740 --> 00:44:22.940 align:middle line:90%
to their discoveries.

00:44:22.940 --> 00:44:24.170 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Yes.

00:44:24.170 --> 00:44:27.622 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And that is what's
been lost in modern science.

00:44:27.622 --> 00:44:28.580 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Very much.

00:44:28.580 --> 00:44:32.300 align:middle line:84%
And the pioneers, both of
relativity and quantum physics,

00:44:32.300 --> 00:44:36.440 align:middle line:84%
were generally
natural philosophers.

00:44:36.440 --> 00:44:40.360 align:middle line:84%
Max Planck, for instance,
Einstein, of course,

00:44:40.360 --> 00:44:43.110 align:middle line:90%
and many others--

00:44:43.110 --> 00:44:45.980 align:middle line:84%
Planck talked about
mind being primary.

00:44:45.980 --> 00:44:49.100 align:middle line:84%
I think he absolutely understood
they're not just primary,

00:44:49.100 --> 00:44:50.510 align:middle line:90%
but is, you know?

00:44:50.510 --> 00:44:52.070 align:middle line:90%
Everything is mine.

00:44:52.070 --> 00:44:56.540 align:middle line:84%
John Archibald Wheeler, who
coined the term black holes,

00:44:56.540 --> 00:44:57.930 align:middle line:90%
talked of it.

00:44:57.930 --> 00:45:01.690 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the appearance,
the physical world, from bit--

00:45:01.690 --> 00:45:03.200 align:middle line:90%
from digitized information.

00:45:03.200 --> 00:45:07.520 align:middle line:84%
And now we're realizing
that it is bit.

00:45:07.520 --> 00:45:10.280 align:middle line:84%
So there have been
scientists and pioneers

00:45:10.280 --> 00:45:15.470 align:middle line:84%
all the way through who have
really not just reconciled,

00:45:15.470 --> 00:45:18.590 align:middle line:84%
but fully integrated
this perspective.

00:45:18.590 --> 00:45:21.350 align:middle line:84%
And yet, I think you're
absolutely right.

00:45:21.350 --> 00:45:22.326 align:middle line:90%
We know this.

00:45:22.326 --> 00:45:24.950 align:middle line:84%
I think the thing that happens,
and certainly over the last few

00:45:24.950 --> 00:45:29.280 align:middle line:84%
generations-- and it was
certainly beginning when I was

00:45:29.280 --> 00:45:31.520 align:middle line:84%
at Oxford back in
the early '70s--

00:45:31.520 --> 00:45:35.990 align:middle line:84%
was this use of science
to support technologies.

00:45:35.990 --> 00:45:39.840 align:middle line:84%
And, in fact, scientists became
more and more technologists.

00:45:39.840 --> 00:45:41.480 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
survey done recently

00:45:41.480 --> 00:45:44.780 align:middle line:84%
of quantum physicists asking
what their interest was

00:45:44.780 --> 00:45:46.370 align:middle line:90%
in the nature of reality.

00:45:46.370 --> 00:45:48.980 align:middle line:84%
And a disturbingly
high proportion

00:45:48.980 --> 00:45:50.180 align:middle line:90%
said they didn't care.

00:45:50.180 --> 00:45:51.215 align:middle line:84%
And these are
quantum physicists.

00:45:51.215 --> 00:45:52.010 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Ooh, ooh, ooh.

00:45:52.010 --> 00:45:53.590 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: These are the
geeks of geeks, you know?

00:45:53.590 --> 00:45:54.010 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's dangerous.

00:45:54.010 --> 00:45:55.790 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: And if quantum
physicists don't have

00:45:55.790 --> 00:45:58.520 align:middle line:84%
a curiosity and a willingness
to go where the evidence leads,

00:45:58.520 --> 00:46:00.690 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the
nature of reality,

00:46:00.690 --> 00:46:03.500 align:middle line:84%
the other scientists just
fall off the back of that.

00:46:03.500 --> 00:46:05.130 align:middle line:90%
That is dangerous.

00:46:05.130 --> 00:46:09.260 align:middle line:10%
And I was both saddened
to hear that, but also I

00:46:09.260 --> 00:46:11.720 align:middle line:10%
think the younger physicists--

00:46:11.720 --> 00:46:15.440 align:middle line:10%
physicists and scientists get
in because they are curious.

00:46:15.440 --> 00:46:18.200 align:middle line:84%
But often they're told, and
they're in environments,

00:46:18.200 --> 00:46:21.290 align:middle line:84%
that they're not allowed
to follow the evidence.

00:46:21.290 --> 00:46:22.910 align:middle line:84%
Because it's going
to lead to places

00:46:22.910 --> 00:46:26.640 align:middle line:84%
that the vested interests
and the people with status

00:46:26.640 --> 00:46:29.630 align:middle line:84%
and all the rest of it
don't want it to go.

00:46:29.630 --> 00:46:31.040 align:middle line:90%
And Thomas Kuhn, of course--

00:46:31.040 --> 00:46:35.450 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS]---- who coined the word
paradigm shift talked about

00:46:35.450 --> 00:46:38.870 align:middle line:84%
paradigm shifts progressing
through funerals.

00:46:38.870 --> 00:46:41.730 align:middle line:84%
I hope we don't need to do that,
because this is too urgent.

00:46:41.730 --> 00:46:42.900 align:middle line:90%
This is too important.

00:46:42.900 --> 00:46:44.820 align:middle line:90%
This isn't about just science.

00:46:44.820 --> 00:46:46.550 align:middle line:90%
It's about all of us.

00:46:46.550 --> 00:46:48.240 align:middle line:90%
How do we live our lives?

00:46:48.240 --> 00:46:50.667 align:middle line:84%
How do we see ourselves
in each other?

00:46:50.667 --> 00:46:52.750 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, I have
great faith in the younger

00:46:52.750 --> 00:46:55.083 align:middle line:84%
generation-- the millennials
and younger, in particular.

00:46:55.083 --> 00:46:56.550 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Me too.

00:46:56.550 --> 00:46:59.120 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because they're not
necessarily buying the status

00:46:59.120 --> 00:47:02.124 align:middle line:84%
quo on any level anymore,
and so their minds are free

00:47:02.124 --> 00:47:03.290 align:middle line:90%
to contemplate these things.

00:47:03.290 --> 00:47:07.190 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it'll take the
death of their forerunners.

00:47:07.190 --> 00:47:09.020 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
go there anyway.

00:47:09.020 --> 00:47:10.160 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: I agree.

00:47:10.160 --> 00:47:13.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's what, for
me, is so exciting, that I'm

00:47:13.100 --> 00:47:13.920 align:middle line:90%
realizing.

00:47:13.920 --> 00:47:16.760 align:middle line:84%
And I think we were talking
earlier, there are so many

00:47:16.760 --> 00:47:20.330 align:middle line:84%
shoots off this, what I
call, a unity awareness.

00:47:20.330 --> 00:47:24.560 align:middle line:84%
And unity consciousness is
really gaining traction.

00:47:24.560 --> 00:47:30.290 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So let's look at the
notion that our reality is more

00:47:30.290 --> 00:47:34.040 align:middle line:84%
and more being likened to
a gigantic computer model

00:47:34.040 --> 00:47:38.840 align:middle line:84%
of reality, randomly
generated information,

00:47:38.840 --> 00:47:39.920 align:middle line:90%
as a computer model.

00:47:39.920 --> 00:47:41.711 align:middle line:84%
Because more people
are understanding that,

00:47:41.711 --> 00:47:43.820 align:middle line:90%
that this is a digital reality.

00:47:43.820 --> 00:47:46.010 align:middle line:90%
That it is an illusion.

00:47:46.010 --> 00:47:48.290 align:middle line:84%
That what we see and
experience is an illusion.

00:47:48.290 --> 00:47:50.270 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about the
difference in the way

00:47:50.270 --> 00:47:53.360 align:middle line:84%
you see that, quote,
"illusion," versus the way

00:47:53.360 --> 00:47:56.360 align:middle line:84%
that the people that are
looking at it in a digital sense

00:47:56.360 --> 00:47:58.490 align:middle line:90%
see that illusion.

00:47:58.490 --> 00:48:01.100 align:middle line:84%
>> CURRIVAN: Well, first of all,
I'd argue the word illusion.

00:48:01.100 --> 00:48:02.680 align:middle line:84%
Because often
people say the word

00:48:02.680 --> 00:48:05.330 align:middle line:84%
"maya," which is an
ancient Indian word that

00:48:05.330 --> 00:48:07.850 align:middle line:90%
can be translated as illusion.

00:48:07.850 --> 00:48:10.385 align:middle line:84%
It can also be
translated as partial.

00:48:10.385 --> 00:48:11.510 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, interesting.

00:48:11.510 --> 00:48:11.840 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:48:11.840 --> 00:48:12.640 align:middle line:90%
>> CURRIVAN: Yes.

00:48:12.640 --> 00:48:15.770 align:middle line:84%
